[src:progressive-web-apps/beforeinstallpromptevent] The **`BeforeInstallPromptEvent`** is the interface of the `beforeinstallprompt` event fired at the `Window` object before a user is prompted to "install" a website to a home screen on mobile.
[src:progressive-web-apps/beforeinstallpromptevent] This interface inherits from the `Event` interface.
[src:progressive-web-apps/beforeinstallpromptevent] Creates a new `BeforeInstallPromptEvent` object.
[src:progressive-web-apps/beforeinstallpromptevent] Returns an array of string items containing the platforms on which the event was dispatched.
[src:progressive-web-apps/beforeinstallpromptevent] This is provided for user agents that want to present a choice of versions to the user such as, for example, "web" or "play" which would allow the user to choose between a web version or an Android version.
[src:progressive-web-apps/beforeinstallpromptevent] Returns a `Promise` that resolves to an object describing the user's choice when they were prompted to install the app.
